ay to a local shrine.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"spot\",\n      \"title\": \"Visiting the Historic Osaka Tenmangu Shrine\",\n      \"block_id\": \"92xUh7sl\",\n      \"location\": {\n        \"lat\": 34.6960904,\n        \"lng\": 135.5127654\n      },\n      \"smart_tags\": [\n        \"#shrine\",\n        \"#cultural-site\",\n        \"#historical\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"Visiting one of Japan's most important shrines, dedicated to the Shinto deity Tenjin, which has been around since the 10th century.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"food\",\n      \"title\": \"Takoyaki and Yakisoba at Shugetsu\",\n      \"block_id\": \"EQhh2X3p\",\n      \"location\": null,\n      \"smart_tags\": [\n        \"#takoyaki\",\n        \"#yakisoba\",\n        \"#osaka-street-food\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"Continuing the food tour at a takoyaki house. Trying different flavors of takoyaki and shio yakisoba (salt-flavored fried noodles).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"food\",\n      \"title\": \"Final Izakaya Stop for Kushikatsu Skewers\",\n      \"block_id\": \"Bc5Rmwa9\",\n      \"location\": null,\n      \"smart_tags\": [\n        \"#kushikatsu\",\n        \"#skewers\",\n        \"#food-hall\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"Finishing the izakaya hopping adventure at a kushikatsu bar in the Lucua Shopping Center Food Hall, eating skewed meat and vegetables.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"transport\",\n      \"title\": \"Saying Goodbye at the Shinkansen Station\",\n      \"block_id\": \"d-AaSYur\",\n      \"location\": null,\n      \"smart_tags\": [\n        \"#shinkansen\",\n        \"#bullet-train\",\n        \"#travel\"\n      ],\n      \"description\": \"Concluding the day by seeing a friend off as she boards the Shinkansen bullet train to go home after a fun day of izakaya hopping.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"videoId\": \"re7H1xsqG8Q\",\n  \"videoUrl\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=re7H1xsqG8Q\",\n  \"spotCount\": 2,\n  \"blockCount\"